cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with object recognition and image formation, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel tensor model and factorization approach for representing the hierarchical causal structure of object appearance, which is a machine learning task (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the interpretability and robustness of the proposed approach, which are important aspects of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses synthetic images for training and reports results on real-world datasets, which suggests the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) in the implementation of the proposed approach.
